org.tagaprice.core.entities
Class Category

java.lang.Object
  org.tagaprice.core.entities.Category
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
@Entity
public class Category
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class represents a category, used to categorize for example Products. But this class is not limited to Products only, in fact it can be used to categorize any entity.

Every Category object has a parent, which may be null. A Category is a node in a simple tree where the root-node has null as its parent.

A Category has the following properties:

  • Id: primary identifier in the database
  • parent: parent category
  • title: short text to represent this category
  • createdAt: date this category was created
  • creator: Account who created this category

This class is immutable. Properties once set, cannot be changed.

Initialize a new Category.

Parameters:
id - Id of the category to create. Can be null, then this category is treated as new concerning the database and a fresh id will be created and assigned. If id is not null it must be greater than 0.
title - Short text to represent this category.
parent - Parent category node. may be null to create a root node.
createdAt - Date this category was created.
creator - Account who created this category.
